---
description: 
globs: 
alwaysApply: true
---
- Read the improvements in the Unreleased section in the changelog file
- Get the current version number in package.json
- Set a new version number according to the changes in the Unreleased section
- Change the Unreleased name to the new version number
- Update version from package.json
- Update version in package.json
> Increase version of an annotated tag `"version": "x.y.z",`
- Update dependencies via run following command npm update
- Commit changes
> git add package.json package-lock.json
> git commit -m "Bump version to x.y.z"
- Create tag
> git tag -a vx.y.z -m "Release version x.y.z"
- Push changes and tags
> git push && git push --tags
